parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clock spring can cause the airbag light to illuminate constantly, indicating a potential malfunction of the airbag system, which can lead to the failure of the airbags to deploy in the event of a crash, increasing the risk of injury or fatality.
symptoms: The airbag light illuminates constantly after the vehicle has been started.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbags to deploy in the event of a crash can increase the risk of injury or fatality to the occupants.
symptoms: The airbags fail to deploy during a frontal crash
